OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778497375
OL,3,CServices commemorate fishermen lost at
OL,4,Csea
OL,6,FRichard Slee reports from Weymouth,
OL,7,Fwhere families gathered to remember
OL,8,Floved ones lost at sea.
OL,10,FToday marks the third annual National
OL,11,FFishing Remembrance Day, recognising
OL,12,Fthat fishing is now considered the
OL,13,Fmost dangerous peacetime occupation.
OL,15,FFamily members and friends of those
OL,16,Fwho've been lost at sea gathered at
OL,17,Fservices across the south to pay their
OL,18,Frespects.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/6
