PN,41504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778497375
OL,3,CServices commemorate fishermen lost at
OL,4,Csea
OL,6,FDavid McFarlane, Jack Craig, and
OL,7,FRobert Prowse were among those being
OL,8,Fremembered in the town today.
OL,10,FHayley Hamlett from the Fisherman's
OL,11,FMission Charity said: "Fishermen, when
OL,12,Fthey're out day on day, the situation
OL,13,Fand the conditions can change
OL,14,Fincredibly rapidly.
OL,16,FThe modern fishing boats also work
OL,17,Fwith some very powerful equipment,
OL,18,Fhauliers, net hauliers, winches and
OL,19,Fthat sort of thing.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778497375
OL,3,CServices commemorate fishermen lost at
OL,4,Csea
OL,6,F"And you really have to have your wits
OL,7,Fabout you and, to not only be an
OL,8,Faccomplished mariner, but also to
OL,9,Funderstand the equipment that you're
OL,10,Fusing, that can unfortunately, be
OL,11,Ffatal at times."
OL,13,FHayley Guille is the daughter, and
OL,14,Fgranddaughter of fishermen, and was in
OL,15,FWeymouth with her mum Josie.
OL,17,FShe said every day was a struggle to
OL,18,Fmake a living: "Price of bait, fuel,
OL,19,Feverything is just going like with,
OL,20,Fyou know, general food shopping.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1778497375
OL,3,CServices commemorate fishermen lost at
OL,4,Csea
OL,6,F"Everything is going up and up and up
OL,7,Fand there's no guarantee what you're
OL,8,Fgoing to earn. You could work as hard
OL,9,Fas you can and still come out with
OL,10,Fnext to nothing."
OL,12,FThe service ended with a prayer and
OL,13,Fthen a bell was rung to mark the start
OL,14,Fof a minute's silence.
OL,16,FFloral tributes were left at the
OL,17,Fquayside, where a memorial stone is
OL,18,Fplanned, and roses were cast onto the
OL,19,Fwater, to remember the local fishermen
OL,20,Fwho've lost their lives.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/6
